# Deployment Policy: Vercel Only

When deploying changes to this project, **ONLY use Vercel** for deployments.

## Deployment Method

Vercel automatically deploys when changes are pushed to GitHub:

```bash
# ✅ CORRECT: Push to GitHub (Vercel auto-deploys)
git add .
git commit -m "Your commit message"
git push origin main
```

## What NOT to Do

```bash
# ❌ NEVER run these commands:
npm run deploy          # Deploys to GitHub Pages
npm run predeploy       # Builds for GitHub Pages
gh-pages -d dist        # Manual GitHub Pages deployment
```

## Why Vercel Only?

- **Single source of truth**: https://my-mobile-app-taupe.vercel.app/
- **Automatic deployments**: Vercel auto-deploys on git push
- **No manual deploy step**: Just commit and push to GitHub

## Summary

1. Make code changes
2. Commit changes with git
3. Push to GitHub with `git push origin main`
4. Vercel automatically deploys (no additional commands needed)
